Jun 18 2009 	Friendly family	Managed by a friendly and extremely helpful Indian family and staffed by a mix of Polish and Brit workers, the basic B&amp;B hotel scores from the point of view of location and cost, two crucial reasons that drew me to the place, apart from the Indian connection.The location is convenient, in west central London and within a couple of minutes walking distance from the tube station though the sound of the passing trains can be intrusive. As for the tariffs, the starting price of 39 pounds for a single basic room is competitive in frightfully expensive London. But the frugal though clean room is cramped and squeezing into bed is a good work out for the contortionist. It’s great if you want to a place to crash at night but for added ‘value’ and creature comforts, be prepared to lighten your wallet for something more substantial somewhere else.	
