Mar 12 2007	Great location for public transport	I stayed at this hotel for 8 nights in Jan 2007. The immediate area is literally door-to-door hotels so I moved to this hotel after they offered me a good bargain on a double room. They even gave me free access to their wireless internet. They really should publicly offer WiFi as a patron incentive since it basically cost them nothing and the surrounding hotels seem to want to charge for it. Breakfast is only available from 7-9am which is not always convenient. My room was quite nice although they seem to be a bit stingy with towel replacement and soap.The Paddington area is a great place to stay for its transport connections. The tube station and various bus lines are a really short block away. Bus #15 is good to get to many of the popular London attractions. Heathrow Express is also right there.This hotel is far from the finest I've ever stayed at but London nowadays is really expensive (for Americans in particular). I think this hotel offers good basic value for the money. If your really picky about your accommodations, there are other hotels in the area (obviously for more money) that you could choose.	
